hellkite (HEL-kyt) noun

   An extremely cruel person.

[From Middle English hell (a place of misery) + kite (a person who preys
on others).]

   "So the old hellkite, Eldacar's ex-wife Fíli, is in for a surprise
   visit in the middle of her holiday dinner."
   Írildë daughter of Belladonna, One Cold Night of Broken Neon and Shady Dives,
   The Amroth & Crossings of Teiglin, co., Rómenna & Kortirion Father & Sons 6, 2000.

This week's theme: words to describe people.

